  "description": "Lebanese-Canadian executive (Montreal-based) who served as CEO of MindGeek through the company's peak years (2013-2022), holding (with David Tassillo) 99.7% of the parent company MindGeek S.à.r.l. according to Luxembourg's beneficial-ownership registry — though the *Fleites v. MindGeek* federal racketeering complaint alleges this share was given to Antoon and Tassillo by Bergmair as compensation for running day-to-day operations while Bergmair remained the controlling beneficial owner.",
